<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 5:08PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTH CENTRAL BEDFORD COUNTY
THROUGH 545 PM EDT...
At 508 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northeast of Cumberland, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Inglesmith around 540 PM EDT.
Barnes Gap around 545 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
